public class Destinations
extends java.lang.Object
implements IConstants

This class keeps a list of valid destinations for internal links to avoid problems when the PDF is created.

createDestination

public static com.lowagie.text.Phrase createDestination(java.lang.String label,
                                                        com.sun.javadoc.ProgramElementDoc doc,
                                                        com.lowagie.text.Font font)
Creates a destination in the document. This method does nothing if the given destination is invalid.

This method creates a phrase with one or two empty chunks who only serve as holders for the destinations.

Parameters:
label - The label for the destination.
doc - The javadoc element for which to create a destination.
font - The font for the label.
Returns:
The Phrase with the destination in it.
